## Introduction

A hunter is a user who hunts for bounties and then checks in to them.


## Object

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
`id` | `int` | unique identifier
`email` | `string`
`first_name` | `string`
`last_name` | `string`
`balance` | `string` | How many bitcoins the hunter has.

<%= json :hunter %>


## Create (Register)

    POST /hunters

### Input

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
`email` | `string` | **Required**
`password` | `string` | **Required**
`first_name` | `string` | If a name is not provided then a random name will be assigned.
`last_name` | `string` | If a name is not provided then a random name will be assigned.


## Login with Facebook

Returns an access token, same as the regular login view.

    POST /hunters/facebook

### Input

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
`access_token` | `string` | access token returned from the facebook sdk.

## Retrieve Current Hunter

    GET /hunter


